        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 3 at 5:16PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 516 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Northstar, or near Prosser Creek Reservoir, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boca Reservoir, Northstar, Glenshire-Devonshire Cdp, Hirschdale,
Truckee, Alpine Meadows Campground, Glenshire-Devonshire, and
Truckee-Tahoe Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
